But most women have to put
a little time and effort...

02:06.440 --> 02:07.940
Into their appearance.

02:09.060 --> 02:10.490
And then, there are those of us...

02:10.520 --> 02:12.450
Who need all the help
we can get.

02:13.870 --> 02:15.240
Like me.

03:04.100 --> 03:05.930
Tonight my husband
is taking me...

03:05.960 --> 03:08.160
To a very fancy affair...

03:09.280 --> 03:12.050
So I'm going to do
whatever it takes to look great.

03:14.320 --> 03:17.310
Sometimes you just have
to pull out all the staff.

04:23.730 --> 04:25.940
Yet another magnificent
miniseries...

04:25.960 --> 04:28.090
Based on the
passionate prose of...

04:28.120 --> 04:30.800
The reigning Royal Highness
of romance...

04:30.950 --> 04:33.020
Her Majesty Mary Fisher.

04:33.380 --> 04:35.560
At the tender age of 34...

04:35.630 --> 04:38.450
She has already penned
over 30 novels!

04:38.710 --> 04:41.460
These steamy stories
have sold in the millions...

04:41.600 --> 04:43.120
Affording Mary a lifestyle...

04:43.240 --> 04:45.950
Even her wealthiest heroine
would envy.

04:46.370 --> 04:48.840
Here, in her lavish
Long Island Palace...

04:49.030 --> 04:51.420
Mary lives in the lap of luxury.

04:51.650 --> 04:52.660
Passion!

04:53.090 --> 04:54.200
Excitement!

04:54.680 --> 04:57.410
I think that's important
in a long term relationship.

04:58.000 --> 05:01.280
And that's what I think women
find from my novels, a...

05:01.470 --> 05:03.230
They find ways to...

05:03.580 --> 05:05.360
Make their men feel...

05:05.560 --> 05:07.190
Important and comfortable...

05:07.230 --> 05:09.410
So that he knows
that he is...

05:09.760 --> 05:10.770
The man...

05:11.170 --> 05:13.070
You know, so
there's no confusion.

05:13.950 --> 05:15.490
Ever the faithful daughter...

05:15.520 --> 05:18.160
Mary is never too busy
to visit with her mother.

05:18.290 --> 05:20.060
Who convalesces in style...

05:20.090 --> 05:22.030
At the Golden Twilight
rest home.

05:22.270 --> 05:25.550
Mrs. Francine Fisher
is the proud matriarch...

05:25.570 --> 05:26.870
Of the Fisher clan.

05:28.350 --> 05:31.580
Champagne, caviar
and dashing men.

05:32.090 --> 05:33.160
Sit down!

05:33.760 --> 05:34.690
Mary Fisher...

05:34.720 --> 05:37.510
Takes a moment to reflect on
her writing philosophy...

05:37.680 --> 05:38.800
Mr. Patchett...

05:38.820 --> 05:40.780
I got your wife
on line three.

05:45.120 --> 05:46.200
Hello, Ruth!

05:46.260 --> 05:47.550
Hi, honey!

05:47.610 --> 05:49.670
How's my favorite
accountant doing today?

05:49.920 --> 05:52.320
Oh, I'm swamped,
my secretary quit...

05:52.350 --> 05:53.520
I'm going out of my mind...

05:53.540 --> 05:55.200
I'm trying to break
in a new girl...

05:55.460 --> 05:57.200
Oh, well, I just called
to tell you...

05:57.230 --> 05:59.850
How excited I'm
about the party tonight!

05:59.880 --> 06:02.140
Ruth, I'm warning you!
It's going to be very boring.

06:02.170 --> 06:03.920
A bunch of people
I don't really even know.

06:03.950 --> 06:05.720
I just want to do
some networking...

06:05.750 --> 06:07.350
Trying to round up
some new clients...

06:07.380 --> 06:08.200
I don't think it's...

06:08.220 --> 06:10.930
Worth your time to drive
all the way into the city.

06:11.230 --> 06:12.820
Oh, I don't mind!

06:13.130 --> 06:15.440
We haven't been out
together for so long!

06:15.680 --> 06:17.610
Okay, Ruth.
Don't say I didn't warn you!

06:17.640 --> 06:18.730
I got to run, okay sweety?

06:18.860 --> 06:19.570
Bye, bye!

06:19.780 --> 06:20.770
Bye, Bob!

07:09.500 --> 07:10.630
How did you get here?

07:10.660 --> 07:13.160
Oh, I took the Concorde.
It was a little cramped.

07:26.110 --> 07:27.760
Oh, I'm so sorry!

07:28.680 --> 07:30.150
Oh, my God!

07:30.180 --> 07:31.470
It's you!

07:31.490 --> 07:32.450
I don't believe it!

07:32.770 --> 07:34.310
- Oh, I'm so sorry!
- You've ruined my...

07:34.340 --> 07:36.110
Ruth, what are you doing?

07:36.210 --> 07:37.620
Bob, I just spilled
my wine...

07:37.650 --> 07:39.610
On the famous
author Mary Fisher!

07:39.640 --> 07:41.300
I have read
all of your books!

07:41.330 --> 07:43.080
- That's very nice!
- Ruth, why don't you go get...

07:43.110 --> 07:45.340
Some salt and some Perrier
to remove the stain?

07:45.580 --> 07:47.160
Hurry, honey, hurry!

07:59.450 --> 08:01.600
Salt and Perrier!
A man...

08:02.350 --> 08:04.380
Familiar with a woman's domain...

08:04.840 --> 08:05.890
I like that!

08:06.240 --> 08:08.270
It's just that my wife is
always toppling things.

08:08.340 --> 08:10.540
- She's a bit clumsy.
- That's your wife?

08:10.860 --> 08:12.640
- Too bad!
- Yeah...

08:12.760 --> 08:14.040
It's too late!

08:14.400 --> 08:17.470
That stain has already set.
Why don't we just cover it up?

08:18.020 --> 08:20.620
I insist that you send
the bill for the dry cleaning.

08:21.760 --> 08:22.670
I'm sorry.

08:23.510 --> 08:24.950
It's very gallant!

08:26.630 --> 08:29.020
Now I need
another drink, Mr.?

08:29.290 --> 08:31.160
I'm Patchett,
Bob Patchett.

08:33.270 --> 08:34.480
Mr. Patchett.

08:36.840 --> 08:39.520
Hey, can I have some
salt and Perrier?

08:40.010 --> 08:42.539
I just knocked my wine
on Mary Fisher.

08:42.559 --> 08:44.430
You know, the famous author?

08:46.310 --> 08:49.320
What is it exactly that
you do, Mr. Patchett?

08:49.350 --> 08:51.220
- I'm a financial consultant.
- Really?

08:51.240 --> 08:51.940
Yeah!

08:52.220 --> 08:53.430
Oh, I'm filled with awe...

08:53.460 --> 08:54.930
For men who know how
to handle money!

08:55.420 --> 08:57.200
I can't even balance
my own checkbook!

08:57.330 --> 08:59.320
Doesn't your accountant
do that for you?

09:00.320 --> 09:01.400
Should he?

09:01.850 --> 09:03.840
The good ones do.
Actually, Miss Fisher...

09:03.870 --> 09:06.410
I'm moving heavily into
artists management.

09:06.530 --> 09:10.230
I like to be around creative types.
I find it very... stimulating.

09:11.000 --> 09:12.780
Stimulated accounting
sounds...

09:13.310 --> 09:14.880
Very interesting!

09:15.790 --> 09:17.500
Tell me more,
Mr. Patchett.

09:18.750 --> 09:21.490
I refuse to divulge any more
information about myself...

09:21.520 --> 09:23.650
Unless you call me Bob.

09:24.660 --> 09:25.900
All right!

09:26.590 --> 09:28.230
If you promise to call me...

09:28.890 --> 09:29.910
Mary.

09:45.770 --> 09:47.660
All the little families...

09:48.420 --> 09:50.030
The mommies and daddies and...

09:50.600 --> 09:51.560
Their little children...

09:51.590 --> 09:53.120
Tucked away for the night!

09:55.320 --> 09:56.870
How lucky they all are!

10:00.030 --> 10:02.030
It's so kind of you
to take me home.

10:02.060 --> 10:03.550
Absolutely no problem!

10:13.670 --> 10:15.050
Now, Ruth, be careful.

10:15.110 --> 10:16.720
I need to drive
from here, okay honey?

10:16.770 --> 10:18.780
Shouldn't we take her
to the door, Bob?

10:18.820 --> 10:21.870
Oh, that's all right, Miss Fisher,
we live just arond the block.

10:21.890 --> 10:23.640
There's no sense in making
an U turn, right sweety?

10:23.670 --> 10:25.650
No, we still have
such a long way to go.

10:26.210 --> 10:27.530
It's another hour to Hamp...

10:28.390 --> 10:29.520
Hamptons!

10:30.040 --> 10:31.120
Are you okay?

10:31.580 --> 10:33.150
Yes, I'm fine.

10:33.270 --> 10:34.920
Are you sure I'm not
putting you out?

10:34.990 --> 10:37.650
Don't be silly!
75 miles is nothing!

10:37.670 --> 10:38.830
Bye, sweety!

10:44.300 --> 10:46.620
It was very nice meeting you,
Ms. Fisher.

10:46.940 --> 10:47.990
It was nice.

10:48.700 --> 10:51.060
Bye, hon!
Drive carefully!##

11:19.250 --> 11:20.840
Mary Fisher.

11:21.520 --> 11:24.210
Mary Fisher is pretty and rich...

11:24.530 --> 11:25.740
And thin!

11:26.100 --> 11:28.340
And writes best selling
books about love.

11:29.760 --> 11:31.090
Fortunately...

11:31.250 --> 11:32.910
I can trust my husband.

11:47.540 --> 11:49.350
My God, this is fantastic!

11:50.300 --> 11:51.820
You should see my
electricity bills.

11:52.100 --> 11:53.160
I'd love to!

11:53.950 --> 11:55.050
You have a moment?

12:07.040 --> 12:08.020
Garcia!

12:08.290 --> 12:09.380
I waited up for you.

12:09.400 --> 12:12.420
It wasn't necessary, grazie.
You may go to bed now.

12:12.490 --> 12:13.600
We'll be all right.

12:14.140 --> 12:15.140
Yes, ma'am.

12:16.240 --> 12:17.310
Would you care for a drink?

12:17.410 --> 12:18.290
I'd love one.

12:31.920 --> 12:32.780
Good night.

12:33.060 --> 12:34.960
Oh, yes! Good night!

12:35.710 --> 12:37.150
'Buenas noches!'

12:44.520 --> 12:47.130
You've got one hell of a
home office deduction, here!

12:47.500 --> 12:48.850
I don't know what you mean.

12:48.970 --> 12:49.830
Cognac?

12:49.870 --> 12:50.640
Sure!

12:50.830 --> 12:52.150
I just mean that
everything in this room...

12:52.180 --> 12:53.550
From floor to ceiling...

12:53.580 --> 12:55.480
Including that... Courvoisier...

12:55.500 --> 12:57.460
Is a tax writeoff.

12:58.560 --> 12:59.280
Is that...

12:59.700 --> 13:00.400
Good?

13:01.100 --> 13:03.010
Yeah!
It's great!

13:04.280 --> 13:06.490
I have not your head
for money matters at all.

13:06.510 --> 13:08.610
I just find it all so terribly, terribly...

13:10.190 --> 13:11.060
Confusing.

13:13.150 --> 13:15.130
You see, I try to think
only beautiful thoughts...

13:15.160 --> 13:17.040
Because then I think that
the beauty will...

13:17.570 --> 13:18.810
Come out in my work.

13:23.040 --> 13:24.960
You must lead a very
glamorous life, Mary.

13:26.450 --> 13:27.690
I suppose so, Bob...

13:28.680 --> 13:30.430
Sometimes sitting here...

13:30.940 --> 13:32.100
Day after day...

13:32.130 --> 13:34.400
Banging away at my keyboard...

13:37.600 --> 13:39.280
Writing can be so...

13:40.550 --> 13:41.880
So lonely.

13:47.090 --> 13:49.250
I guess you got to have a very
vivid imagination...

13:49.280 --> 13:51.190
To write this
romance novels, don't you?

13:53.450 --> 13:54.630
Yes, I do.

13:59.690 --> 14:01.310
But I also do a lot of...

14:03.420 --> 14:04.560
Research.

14:22.930 --> 14:25.260
" She entwined her
limbs about him..."

14:25.290 --> 14:28.650
"As ivy may wrap itself
around some massive pillar."

14:29.000 --> 14:30.830
"When his love nectar was spent..."

14:30.860 --> 14:33.560
"They drifted into the bliss of sleep."

14:56.190 --> 14:58.440
Maybe he had an accident
and got amnesia.

14:58.850 --> 15:00.190
Don't be a jerk!

15:00.340 --> 15:01.570
If he lost his memory...

15:01.590 --> 15:04.530
The people at the hospital
would just look in his wallet.

15:05.260 --> 15:07.190
And what if his car
slipped off the road...

15:07.420 --> 15:10.380
And he got smashed into
little bloody pieces?

15:10.500 --> 15:12.260
Stop talking like that!

15:12.610 --> 15:14.510
Andrew put that animal down!

15:15.280 --> 15:16.970
Your father drove someone home...

15:16.990 --> 15:19.660
And he probably just blew a tyre
on the expressway.

15:19.940 --> 15:21.260
And it got late...

15:24.870 --> 15:25.780
Bob!

15:26.110 --> 15:27.170
Is that you?

15:28.320 --> 15:29.410
Come on, Fuzzy.

15:29.860 --> 15:30.980
Hi, honey!

15:31.920 --> 15:33.000
Where were you?

15:33.030 --> 15:34.350
Oh, you'll never believe
what happened.

15:34.390 --> 15:35.960
I'm headed home on
the expressway...

15:36.070 --> 15:38.000
And KABUM!
The rear tyre blows up!

15:38.340 --> 15:39.820
By the time I got
the damn tyre changed...

15:39.890 --> 15:40.790
It was so late...

15:41.750 --> 15:43.860
I figured I'd better
check into a motel.

15:43.880 --> 15:46.740
You know, I certainly didn't
want to fall asleep at the wheel.

15:47.840 --> 15:48.710
How're you doing, champ?

15:48.740 --> 15:50.380
Why don't you call me?

15:51.820 --> 15:54.010
Oh, you want me to call at 4:30
and woke up the whole house?

15:54.040 --> 15:54.850
Come on!

15:54.880 --> 15:55.840
Good morning, princess!

15:55.870 --> 15:56.960
Good morning!

15:57.050 --> 15:58.160
Boy, am I hungry!

15:58.240 --> 16:00.060
You are in a good mood
this morning!

16:00.840 --> 16:02.430
By the way, I have got
some great news!

16:02.510 --> 16:04.310
I've landed the
Mary Fisher account!

16:06.030 --> 16:07.550
And that's just the beginning!

16:08.410 --> 16:09.710
With Mary Fisher
as my star client...

16:09.740 --> 16:11.200
I'm not just an
accountant, I am...

16:11.220 --> 16:12.360
Business manager!

16:12.440 --> 16:13.220
Daddy...

16:13.300 --> 16:14.510
Are we going to be rich?

16:14.530 --> 16:15.400
Right away, princess!

16:15.420 --> 16:17.200
- All right!
- All right!

16:23.290 --> 16:26.730
My husband is having an
affair with Mary Fisher!

16:27.420 --> 16:28.510
Ruth, how can you say that?

16:28.540 --> 16:30.460
I've always been totally
honest with you.

16:30.560 --> 16:32.010
You are my best friend!

16:32.680 --> 16:35.270
What's going on between me and Mary
is purely professional.

16:35.300 --> 16:38.100
I would never, ever do anything
to hurt you and the kids.

16:38.470 --> 16:39.940
Come on, honey!

16:41.310 --> 16:42.580
Trust me!

16:46.040 --> 16:49.980
Mary Fisher, I hope your
pink palace crumbles into the sea...

16:50.100 --> 16:52.910
I hope your delicate white skin
breaks up in hives...

16:52.940 --> 16:55.600
And your shiny blond hair
falls off at the roots!

16:57.950 --> 16:59.380
But meanwhile...

16:59.510 --> 17:00.580
I will watch...

17:00.990 --> 17:02.030
And wait.

17:03.580 --> 17:06.020
I will keep busy in
taking care of our home.

17:08.450 --> 17:11.010
I will try to look attractive
for my husband.

17:12.450 --> 17:14.349
Bob's just going into a phase...

17:14.520 --> 17:16.349
And when it's over, I'll be here.

17:16.520 --> 17:18.420
Ready and waiting for him.

17:19.369 --> 17:21.829
Mary Fisher, you are just a fling.

17:22.089 --> 17:24.660
A novelty, an infatuation.

17:25.010 --> 17:26.460
Bob doesn't love you!

17:26.540 --> 17:27.730
I love you!

17:38.660 --> 17:42.240
I know my husband better
than you ever will, Mary Fisher.

17:42.760 --> 17:45.090
And I know what to do
to win him back!

17:46.390 --> 17:47.870
"The art of winning back
your man...

17:47.940 --> 17:51.700
Is easy with these surefire
economical, sexy recipes.

17:52.030 --> 17:53.500
"The secret of
Chicken Vol-au-Vent...

17:53.520 --> 17:55.080
Is a delicate, puff pastry.

17:55.170 --> 17:56.770
The perfect appetizer
for this dish...

17:56.830 --> 17:59.460
Is a smooth, seductive,
mushroom soup."

18:00.040 --> 18:01.040
Gross!

18:01.060 --> 18:02.900
Your father loves
mushroom soup.

18:03.150 --> 18:04.320
We don't love it!

18:04.340 --> 18:05.840
We are eating too, aren't we?

18:05.960 --> 18:09.130
Yes, but tonight we want
to make your father very happy.

18:09.220 --> 18:10.030
Why?

18:10.190 --> 18:11.740
So he'll stay at home?

18:34.180 --> 18:35.380
Was that...

18:35.610 --> 18:37.170
Was that for real
or the wildest dreaming?

18:37.610 --> 18:38.850
If this is a dream...

18:39.190 --> 18:40.850
I don't ever want
to wake up.

18:46.270 --> 18:47.190
Wow...

18:47.210 --> 18:48.440
I know!

18:49.390 --> 18:50.990
What are you doing now?

18:51.010 --> 18:52.480
Oh, what are you now...?

18:57.120 --> 18:58.390
What are you doing?

18:58.500 --> 18:59.740
I got to go home!

19:00.580 --> 19:01.740
Already?

19:01.780 --> 19:03.630
Yeah... Myr parents
are coming home for dinner.

19:05.000 --> 19:07.680
I didn't realize that you
were so domestic.

19:07.750 --> 19:09.550
Come on, I got
to get home sometimes!

19:10.500 --> 19:11.200
No!

19:11.320 --> 19:12.680
You know you don't!

19:13.700 --> 19:15.710
You don't ever
have to go back, Bob.

19:15.990 --> 19:17.990
We fell in love!
It's no one's fault!

19:18.010 --> 19:20.280
It's not your fault.
It's not my fault.

19:21.030 --> 19:22.310
I know when you
married Ruth you...

19:22.460 --> 19:24.350
You did it out of
for kindness, and pity...

19:24.370 --> 19:25.740
And I love you for that...

19:25.900 --> 19:28.600
But Bob now, please, please...

19:29.780 --> 19:31.030
Be kind to me!

19:31.050 --> 19:34.240
Be with me, stay with me,
live with me!

19:34.360 --> 19:35.210
Mary...

19:35.330 --> 19:37.770
I want to but it's not that easy!
I've got kids!

19:37.800 --> 19:39.600
But they have their mother!

19:41.240 --> 19:43.290
Ruth is blessed
with those children...

19:43.590 --> 19:45.030
They're her pride and joy.

19:45.840 --> 19:47.420
It's not fair!

19:47.990 --> 19:49.130
What do I have?

19:49.150 --> 19:52.000
My all life is so empty!

19:52.420 --> 19:54.400
Don't you say that.
You've got me!

19:57.110 --> 19:59.350
I'm tired of sharing
you with her!

19:59.900 --> 20:01.280
Bob...

20:02.190 --> 20:04.730
I don't think I can stand
that much longer...

20:10.050 --> 20:12.040
I want all of you!

20:14.780 --> 20:15.850
I know.

20:16.960 --> 20:18.200
Damn, if I know.

20:34.270 --> 20:36.190
Hey, daddy is home!

20:39.110 --> 20:40.050
Hi, daddy!

20:40.510 --> 20:41.660
Hi, princess!

20:42.170 --> 20:43.440
Are you sleeping here tonight?

20:43.460 --> 20:45.020
Of course I am, sweety pie!

20:45.100 --> 20:47.550
Your grandparents are coming over,
we're going to have a nice family night.

20:47.570 --> 20:49.230
That ought to be unusual.

20:49.500 --> 20:51.610
Hey, Ruth, dinner
going to be ready on time?

20:51.700 --> 20:53.160
Yes, yes, it will.

20:53.460 --> 20:55.350
Hey, you were supposed
to be home an hour ago.

20:55.380 --> 20:56.940
I could have used some help.

20:57.000 --> 20:58.670
I'm sorry.
I got stuck in a meeting.

20:58.690 --> 21:00.340
I'm going to jump
in the shower.

21:14.910 --> 21:16.250
Oh, Jesus!

21:16.420 --> 21:17.400
Ruth!

21:17.970 --> 21:19.380
What the hell are you doing?

21:20.960 --> 21:22.020
Oh, please...

21:22.150 --> 21:22.840
Don't start now!

21:22.860 --> 21:24.470
My folks are going
to be here soon.

21:24.500 --> 21:25.780
I'm not starting anything.

21:25.800 --> 21:27.440
I'm... going to weigh myself...

21:27.480 --> 21:28.250
Yap!

21:28.550 --> 21:30.030
No wonder you're upset!

21:49.980 --> 21:51.210
Nothing's ready...

21:51.300 --> 21:52.420
And they're here!

21:54.210 --> 21:55.150
They're early.

21:55.180 --> 21:56.000
They're always early!

21:56.250 --> 21:57.880
Cheese and crackers,
that's it?

21:58.630 --> 22:00.790
The flans ought to be ready
in ten minutes.

22:01.100 --> 22:02.910
I'm doing
the best I can, Bob.

22:03.080 --> 22:05.810
Please don't embarrass me
in front of my folks.

22:13.280 --> 22:14.780
What are you doing
down there, son?

22:14.850 --> 22:17.040
- I can't find my gerbil.
- Really?

22:17.060 --> 22:19.070
Well, let grandpa
help you look for it!

22:19.100 --> 22:21.030
- Robin!
- Got to be 'round here somewhere!

22:21.560 --> 22:23.170
There she is!

22:35.670 --> 22:36.990
I've got it, hon!

22:37.190 --> 22:39.360
- Are you okay, dear?
- What's the matter with that woman?

22:39.720 --> 22:41.180
Herbie, are you under there?

22:41.610 --> 22:44.240
- She's clumsy as an ox!
- Is it that time of the month?

22:44.390 --> 22:45.210
Herbie?

22:45.540 --> 22:47.000
I'm going to get back
in the kitchen.

22:47.030 --> 22:48.050
Can I help you?

22:48.080 --> 22:48.860
Relax, mom.

22:48.880 --> 22:51.210
Ruth has got everything under
control, don't you honey?

22:52.560 --> 22:54.080
Andy, find him yet?

23:07.380 --> 23:10.100
Certainly these romantic novels
have universal appeal.

23:10.210 --> 23:11.310
They sell like crazy!

23:11.480 --> 23:12.680
Women... buy it.

23:13.290 --> 23:14.200
Ask Ruth.

23:14.550 --> 23:15.680
She's read everyone!

23:15.970 --> 23:18.060
Nicolette, will you clear
the salad dish, please?

23:18.300 --> 23:19.370
Do I have to?

23:19.490 --> 23:21.070
You men don't understand.

23:21.550 --> 23:22.930
It's always up to the woman...

23:22.960 --> 23:25.010
To keep the romance
in a relationship...

23:25.030 --> 23:26.430
I'm sure Ruth
reads these books...

23:26.460 --> 23:28.490
For inspiration, don't you Ruth?

23:29.270 --> 23:30.420
We don't need books.

23:30.890 --> 23:32.880
Ruth and I have a
terrific relationship.

23:32.980 --> 23:34.560
Always had, always will.

23:34.710 --> 23:35.870
Sure we have our problems...

23:35.990 --> 23:37.470
But it's a question
of give and take.

23:37.640 --> 23:39.220
Once you understand that...

23:39.330 --> 23:40.930
The romance takes care of itself.

23:41.160 --> 23:44.240
Bob, that's so very sensitive
coming from you!

23:44.290 --> 23:46.740
Ruth, I didn't know
he was so sensitive!

23:48.470 --> 23:49.870
Oh, my God!

23:49.950 --> 23:51.160
Herbie!

23:51.320 --> 23:52.480
I'm going to barf!

23:52.870 --> 23:55.020
Ruth, what the hell
is wrong with you?

23:55.050 --> 23:55.990
I'll go get a strainer.

23:56.010 --> 23:57.730
A strainer?
That's a dead rodent!

23:58.330 --> 23:59.580
Take it off the table!

23:59.600 --> 24:01.160
- Bob, calm down!
- Calm down?

24:01.190 --> 24:03.540
The woman is a walking
disaster area!

24:04.270 --> 24:06.270
Why don't you get Mary Fisher
to cook your dinner?

24:06.310 --> 24:07.470
Ruth, I warn you!

24:07.490 --> 24:09.010
She's his mistress, you know?

24:09.070 --> 24:10.220
Shut up, Ruth!

24:13.450 --> 24:14.800
You see what I have
to put up with?

24:15.250 --> 24:17.670
I'll never forgive you for being
so rude to my parents!

24:17.700 --> 24:19.250
Bob, don't be
so mean to her!

24:19.270 --> 24:21.140
Mean? She's the one
making my life miserable.

24:21.170 --> 24:22.500
I knew I never should've
married her!

24:22.530 --> 24:23.550
Bob, the children!

24:23.580 --> 24:25.840
Nicolette and Andy, go up
to your rooms, now, now, now!

24:25.870 --> 24:28.620
Bobby, Bobby, if you didn't love her,
you shouldn't have married her.

24:29.220 --> 24:30.960
Yeah, she was pregnant,
you made me!

24:30.990 --> 24:32.690
Marriage is never easy!

24:33.090 --> 24:34.580
With Ruth, it's not even possible!

24:34.640 --> 24:36.000
Come on, Brenda!
We'll eat out.

24:36.030 --> 24:39.300
That's a good idea, since half
your dinner is on the goddamn floor!

24:46.560 --> 24:49.030
I had every intention
to save this marriage.

24:49.770 --> 24:51.170
I'm tell you something, Ruth.

24:51.250 --> 24:54.170
Life is made up
of assets and liabilies.

24:54.200 --> 24:56.630
As a man I have
four basic assets...

24:56.670 --> 24:59.410
1: A home, that is my castle...

24:59.670 --> 25:02.770
2: A family, that is loving
and devoted...

25:02.810 --> 25:06.130
3: A successful career that
I worked very hard to maintain...

25:06.170 --> 25:09.130
And 4: The freedom to enjoy
the fruits of my labor.

25:09.160 --> 25:11.320
But when it comes to liabillities,
I have only one.

25:11.350 --> 25:12.650
That's you, Ruth!

25:13.250 --> 25:16.770
And I'm not gonna let you ruin everything
I've worked so hard for!

25:17.390 --> 25:18.460
You're a bad mother...

25:18.520 --> 25:19.490
A lousy wife...

25:19.580 --> 25:20.820
And a terrible cook!

25:21.020 --> 25:21.710
In fact...

25:21.740 --> 25:23.550
Have you looked
in a mirror recently?

25:24.040 --> 25:25.400
I don't even think
you're a woman!

25:25.570 --> 25:27.000
Do you know what you are?

25:27.290 --> 25:29.100
You are a she-devil!

26:25.410 --> 26:26.910
Mary Fisher.

26:27.610 --> 26:30.380
Mary Fisher lives in a palace
by the sea.

26:30.790 --> 26:33.630
She is pretty,
and rich and thin!

26:34.010 --> 26:36.750
And in love with my husband,
who's her accountant.

26:37.870 --> 26:39.300
I loved my husband...

26:42.510 --> 26:45.410
And I hate Mary Fisher!

27:04.600 --> 27:06.230
BOB's ASSETS
1. HOME

27:06.260 --> 27:08.120
2. FAMILY
3. CAREER

27:12.410 --> 27:13.700
4. FREEDOM

29:53.370 --> 29:55.090
He is cute, that kid.

29:58.330 --> 29:59.910
It blew up
and then fell down.

30:11.630 --> 30:13.240
Oh, my God!

30:13.310 --> 30:14.890
Mom, what happened?

30:15.410 --> 30:16.420
Well...

30:17.500 --> 30:19.360
We had a little accident.

30:22.580 --> 30:24.160
What about our clothes?

30:24.710 --> 30:25.670
Gone.

30:25.730 --> 30:27.510
- What about my toys?
- Gone.

30:27.540 --> 30:29.000
What about my tapes?

30:29.290 --> 30:31.150
Gone, everything is gone.

30:31.550 --> 30:33.140
Where are we going, Mom?

30:34.080 --> 30:35.220
Mom?

31:14.090 --> 31:14.890
Yes?

31:14.910 --> 31:16.900
I'm Mrs. Ruth Patchett.

31:17.270 --> 31:19.270
Children would like to see
their father.

31:23.010 --> 31:25.180
Oh, please come in.

31:26.080 --> 31:28.010
Why don't you just
go find your father.

31:28.050 --> 31:29.630
There's a door on the way,
to the right.

31:30.430 --> 31:32.190
This place is cool!

31:53.140 --> 31:53.990
Andy!

31:54.490 --> 31:56.130
I found him!

31:56.360 --> 31:57.550
Hi, daddy...

31:57.720 --> 31:59.330
Who let you in here?
Gracia?!

31:59.360 --> 32:01.810
Ruth, what the hell do
you think you're doing?

32:02.130 --> 32:03.980
Andy, Nicolette,
this is your new home...

32:04.010 --> 32:05.860
I'm sure you'll be
very happy here.

32:06.280 --> 32:08.110
Ruth, you are really
depraved!

32:08.150 --> 32:10.490
Someone get this strange
woman out of here!

32:10.560 --> 32:11.630
Garcia!

32:11.750 --> 32:13.230
You take care, kids.

32:13.560 --> 32:15.070
And remember,
no matter what...

32:15.130 --> 32:16.240
I love you both...

32:16.600 --> 32:17.600
Very much.

32:19.310 --> 32:20.100
Ruth!

32:20.530 --> 32:21.350
Ruth...

32:21.730 --> 32:23.130
If this is your idea
of a joke...

32:23.360 --> 32:24.780
It's not funny!

32:25.940 --> 32:27.960
Do you have
a satellite dish?

32:33.400 --> 32:34.240
Ruth!

32:34.380 --> 32:36.220
Ruth, take the children home!

32:36.330 --> 32:37.340
I can't.

32:37.580 --> 32:38.730
If you want to talk,
we'll meet for lunch...

32:38.760 --> 32:40.580
But the children belong
at home with their mother!

32:40.720 --> 32:43.040
You don't understand Bob.
There is no home.

32:43.070 --> 32:44.100
What are you talking about?

32:44.140 --> 32:45.930
The house is gone.
Burned down.

32:46.010 --> 32:48.530
- There's nothing left but ashes.
- I don't believe you.

32:48.550 --> 32:50.810
Well, call the insurance adjuster,
he'll tell you!

32:53.800 --> 32:54.710
Ruth!

32:55.300 --> 32:56.200
Ruth!

32:58.130 --> 32:59.010
Okay...

32:59.320 --> 33:00.270
Okay, Ruth!

33:00.540 --> 33:01.610
I'll give you a few days...

33:01.660 --> 33:03.210
Then you got to
come back for the kids.

33:03.350 --> 33:04.380
Where can I reach you?

33:04.400 --> 33:06.130
I'm not coming back, Bob.

33:06.380 --> 33:08.560
They'll have a much
better life here with you.

33:08.630 --> 33:10.310
Wait a minute, Ruth.
Where are you going?

33:10.330 --> 33:13.030
I don't know, Bob.
Into my future, I guess.

33:13.500 --> 33:14.330
Ruth!

33:15.050 --> 33:15.880
Ruth!

33:16.330 --> 33:17.210
Ruth!

33:17.870 --> 33:20.320
Goddammit! Ruth!

33:22.300 --> 33:23.210
Stop it!

33:37.790 --> 33:40.390
I will have to get used
to being alone now.

33:42.280 --> 33:43.600
It's not easy for a mother...

33:43.640 --> 33:45.730
To be separated
from her children.

33:46.760 --> 33:49.860
I'll bet Mary Fisher's mother
feels the same way.

33:52.050 --> 33:54.080
Maybe I can help
old Mrs. Fisher...

33:54.110 --> 33:56.030
Get reacquainted
with her daughter.

33:59.850 --> 34:00.690
Buy a rose?

34:00.720 --> 34:03.320
A beautiful rose
for a beautiful lady.

34:04.570 --> 34:05.890
But first...

34:06.660 --> 34:08.370
I will need a new name.

34:32.639 --> 34:34.420
The old are all the same.

34:34.440 --> 34:36.940
Allow them nothing!
Take a firm line!

34:36.960 --> 34:39.260
Remember, they're
no different than children.

34:39.420 --> 34:41.070
Are you used to
children, Miss Rose?

34:41.100 --> 34:41.639
Yes.

34:41.670 --> 34:44.070
Good, then you'll feel
right at home here.

34:44.420 --> 34:47.170
Oh, let me stress one thing
above all else.

34:47.270 --> 34:50.360
You must report any damp or
smelling beds immediately.

34:50.480 --> 34:52.560
- Do you mean...
- Incontinence!

34:52.929 --> 34:54.290
Bed wetters have no place...

34:54.310 --> 34:56.460
In the Golden Twilight Home!

34:57.320 --> 34:58.750
Walk this way, please.

35:02.820 --> 35:04.250
Are they sedated?

35:04.580 --> 35:07.600
Our angels would rather sleep
then be awake wondering why...

35:07.620 --> 35:09.390
Their families have
thrown them away...

35:09.430 --> 35:11.380
You can understand that,
can't you, Miss. Rose?

35:11.410 --> 35:12.420
Of course!

35:12.450 --> 35:14.050
Good afternoon,
Mrs. Trumper...

35:14.080 --> 35:16.510
Oh, Mrs. Hooper,
this is Vesta Rose...

35:16.540 --> 35:18.000
She's the new orderly.

35:18.630 --> 35:19.610
Hello!

35:21.030 --> 35:23.410
It's time for their medications.

35:31.390 --> 35:34.880
Nurse Hooper may be short,
but she's very devouted.

35:35.070 --> 35:36.780
Been with me for years!

35:37.330 --> 35:39.010
You'll take your orders
from her.

35:39.420 --> 35:40.650
Now go help her!

35:40.710 --> 35:42.150
Yes, Mrs. Trumper.

35:54.040 --> 35:55.990
That's it!
Good girl.

35:56.690 --> 35:57.760
Not good?

35:58.880 --> 36:00.300
Here we go.
Open up...

36:00.550 --> 36:01.370
Right!

36:02.820 --> 36:04.540
Okay, Mrs. Fisher...

36:04.740 --> 36:06.000
Open wide...

36:07.660 --> 36:09.790
- There we go.
- How are you, Mrs. Fisher?

36:09.990 --> 36:11.610
You look
very pretty today!

36:13.480 --> 36:15.080
All right now, Mrs Palmer...

37:11.720 --> 37:13.470
SEDATIVE

37:26.320 --> 37:27.990
MaxiLIFE

37:34.640 --> 37:38.830
Mary Fisher's mother has been enjoying
a long untroubled sleep...

37:39.510 --> 37:42.220
It was time to wake her up!

38:16.080 --> 38:17.490
Come on!

38:17.540 --> 38:18.970
Give me the ball!

38:19.000 --> 38:19.720
Yeah!

38:20.160 --> 38:20.890
Go!

38:21.980 --> 38:23.820
Come on, Ms. Wolinski!

38:24.700 --> 38:27.980
Vesta, what is going on here?

38:28.000 --> 38:29.430
Oh, is it not wonderful?

38:29.460 --> 38:31.700
I know what you been doing!

38:31.730 --> 38:33.930
The vitamins!
The workouts!

38:33.950 --> 38:35.290
It's against the rules!

38:35.830 --> 38:38.420
I'm going to
report you to Ms. Trumper...

38:38.450 --> 38:39.870
And then you'll be sorry!

38:39.890 --> 38:41.550
Oh, I don't think so!

38:42.410 --> 38:44.570
I have been sorry
my whole life...

38:44.590 --> 38:46.320
And by the looks of it,
so have you!

38:46.450 --> 38:48.160
So you do
whatever you want.

38:50.050 --> 38:51.700
But it's a shame now, Hooper...

38:51.980 --> 38:53.440
I always thought
that women like us...

38:53.460 --> 38:54.730
Should stick together.

38:57.290 --> 38:58.290
Let's go!

38:58.870 --> 39:00.420
Catch that ball!

39:01.580 --> 39:03.930
She knew her body as
if she'd had it for a millennium...

39:03.950 --> 39:07.190
And with an ease neither of them
had ever, ever, known...

39:07.440 --> 39:09.140
He reached for her...

39:09.310 --> 39:10.780
Come Juliet, Fuzzy!

39:10.840 --> 39:11.690
Nub...

39:18.740 --> 39:19.500
No.

39:26.260 --> 39:27.100
Love...

39:27.430 --> 39:28.290
Button...

39:38.850 --> 39:39.820
Nicolette!

39:41.420 --> 39:42.730
Nicolette...

39:44.340 --> 39:45.480
Nicolette!

39:46.130 --> 39:47.400
Nicolette!!

39:51.930 --> 39:52.840
Nicolette!

39:53.250 --> 39:54.330
Nicolette!

39:55.920 --> 39:57.230
I'll call you back later.

39:58.180 --> 39:59.580
You don't have to scream!

39:59.650 --> 40:00.380
I asked you...

40:00.620 --> 40:02.540
10 or 15 times not to...

40:03.090 --> 40:04.830
Play that thing... so loudly.

40:05.140 --> 40:07.860
And you damn know I don't approve
that you're talking on that party line!

40:07.940 --> 40:09.380
There's nothing else
to do around here.

40:13.190 --> 40:13.910
Hello!

40:13.950 --> 40:16.490
Mary, hi!
What's going on out there?

40:16.740 --> 40:19.720
I just spoked to your publisher
she's been trying to reach you.

40:19.740 --> 40:20.250
I know...

40:20.270 --> 40:21.140
The little Nicolette...

40:21.420 --> 40:23.120
Has been on the phone
all day long!

40:23.980 --> 40:25.450
Paula is very upset!

40:25.650 --> 40:28.080
She says the new manuscript
is two months overdue.

40:28.890 --> 40:31.800
You have no idea what
I have to put up with around here!

40:31.820 --> 40:34.720
The noise, the bickering,
the constant interruptions.

40:34.870 --> 40:37.010
I can barely even...
concentrate!

40:37.040 --> 40:38.330
And let alone create!

40:38.470 --> 40:42.170
Mary, Mary, the kids have been
through a very emotional experience...

40:42.770 --> 40:45.210
They need time to adjust
to the new environement.

40:45.440 --> 40:48.450
You're the stepmother, you got
to make them feel at home, Mary!

40:48.680 --> 40:49.710
Help them!

40:49.770 --> 40:51.120
Yes, I know!

40:52.080 --> 40:53.110
Andrew!

40:53.140 --> 40:54.490
Andrew, what are you doing?

40:55.140 --> 40:56.300
Andrew!

40:56.970 --> 40:59.510
Andrew, you leave
little Juliet alone!

40:59.550 --> 41:00.760
Mary, what's on?

41:01.010 --> 41:03.510
Your child and that mongrel
are molesting my dog.

41:04.310 --> 41:05.760
Andrew, did you hear me?

41:06.040 --> 41:06.950
Andrew...

41:07.040 --> 41:08.560
Throw that stick away
right now!

41:08.820 --> 41:09.800
Right now!

41:25.780 --> 41:26.720
Mary...

41:27.110 --> 41:28.180
Mary!

41:28.780 --> 41:29.890
Mary!

41:39.120 --> 41:41.420
It's time for your medication,
Mrs. Fisher..

41:41.460 --> 41:44.390
This is the stupidest piece of trash
I have ever read!

41:44.470 --> 41:45.830
How are you today, dear?

41:45.880 --> 41:47.460
How the hell do I look?

41:47.830 --> 41:50.930
- Better, dear, much better.
- Well, I'm bored to death!

41:51.290 --> 41:53.580
Folk can go crazy
in a place like this!

41:54.080 --> 41:57.260
Well, how about some nice
hearthy beef barley?

41:57.290 --> 41:59.300
Oh, you know
I hate this slop!

42:04.420 --> 42:06.520
You think you can
slip me a beer?

42:15.050 --> 42:17.010
Mary Fisher, any relation?

42:17.180 --> 42:18.330
My daughter!

42:18.500 --> 42:21.180
- Oh how nice!
- She's a slut!

42:21.420 --> 42:23.110
Bitch keeps me
in this dogpound...

42:23.140 --> 42:24.810
While she lives the
life of a princess...

42:24.840 --> 42:26.260
In her goddamn mansion!

42:26.720 --> 42:28.580
Why, that doesn't seem fair!

42:28.600 --> 42:30.730
Yeah I ought to drop in
on her one day...

42:30.790 --> 42:32.820
That'd scare the shit
out of her.

42:32.960 --> 42:34.280
You have rights.

42:34.360 --> 42:37.550
If you wanted to go see your daughter
nobody could stop you.

42:37.930 --> 42:39.360
I'm too old!

42:39.980 --> 42:42.850
You are a mature and
vibrant woman...

42:43.010 --> 42:45.270
And don't you let anybody
tell you anything different.

42:45.390 --> 42:46.270
Yeah?

42:46.330 --> 42:48.920
I suppose I could go
on Sunday afternoon!

42:49.000 --> 42:51.020
I'll put you
on the train myself.

42:51.090 --> 42:54.130
And I'll even call ahead to make sure
the butler knows you're coming.

42:54.390 --> 42:55.580
Butler?

42:55.990 --> 42:58.000
I'll bet there's
hanky panky there!

42:58.500 --> 43:00.380
Well there's only
one way to find out!

43:36.690 --> 43:37.820
- All right?
- Come with me.

43:38.590 --> 43:39.250
All right!

43:39.280 --> 43:40.180
- Here we go!
- Okay.

43:40.210 --> 43:41.340
- Coming your way!
Lift it up!

43:42.840 --> 43:44.220
Kill her!
Allright!

43:44.250 --> 43:46.270
Trash her!
Come on!

43:46.560 --> 43:47.360
Yes!

43:47.390 --> 43:48.570
Kill her again!

43:48.680 --> 43:50.230
Crush her!

43:50.300 --> 43:51.530
Go! Yes!

43:53.270 --> 43:54.530
What a pigsty!

43:55.040 --> 43:56.000
Andrew!

43:56.310 --> 43:57.370
Nicolette!

43:58.010 --> 44:00.340
In this house we do not eat
in the living room!

44:00.850 --> 44:02.850
That's my blouse!
You're wearing my blouse!

44:02.880 --> 44:04.310
I have no clean clothes!

44:04.920 --> 44:06.270
Do the laundry, then!

44:06.300 --> 44:08.680
I'm sure your little brother
will be happy to help you.

44:09.030 --> 44:10.090
I don't know how.

44:10.720 --> 44:12.230
- Oh, yeah!
- Andrew, don't...

44:12.530 --> 44:14.040
Ever kick me again!

44:14.490 --> 44:16.320
- Come back here!
- That's it!

44:16.780 --> 44:18.980
Now, go upstairs and
clean your rooms.

44:19.500 --> 44:20.750
Tell the maid to do it!

44:20.840 --> 44:21.910
You shit!

44:22.420 --> 44:23.750
- Shit!
- Ute! Ute!

44:23.800 --> 44:25.480
- Shit!
- Ute!

44:26.000 --> 44:27.690
Ute, the children...

44:27.750 --> 44:29.670
Don't seem to have
any clean clothes!

44:29.860 --> 44:30.890
Do you think
that you could pos...

44:30.920 --> 44:33.270
Fuzzy has just shit
all over the carpet!

44:33.550 --> 44:35.960
Or perhaps Miss Fisher
would like to clean that up?

44:35.990 --> 44:37.330
And Ute will do the laundry?

44:37.360 --> 44:38.870
No, no, no, that's all right!

44:39.190 --> 44:40.230
Where is Garcia?

44:40.250 --> 44:42.050
In the swimming pool,
where else?

44:43.400 --> 44:44.420
García!

44:50.180 --> 44:51.130
García!

44:54.140 --> 44:56.380
García, what the hell do
you think you're doing?

44:56.520 --> 44:58.040
I'm not really sure.

44:58.620 --> 45:00.730
Lately I haven't been able
to perform my...

45:00.750 --> 45:01.960
Usual services.

45:02.030 --> 45:02.850
Well!

45:03.000 --> 45:04.690
You are still the butler...

